		<label>tlilcoatl</label>
		<description>The tlilcoatl ("black snake" in nahuatl) is a predatory reptile in Mexican folklore. Tlilcoatls have glossy black scales, and grow to a considerable size.\n\nTlilcoatls aren't naturally occurring creatures, and were created as part of the Hecate Project, a bio-engineering program that applied mechanite replicators to already existing animals to mutate them into "magical" creatures.\n\nSpecial Abilities: </description>
